snippet.textDisplay:
This in an opinionated statement. If you feel you are easily offended, then don’t read it.
If you get offended reading it, don’t comment. I’m not here trying to incite drama. Just continue scrolling please and wash your damn hands.
Amidst the existential crisis that is taking place right now, America to put it bluntly, is not prepared at all for what is on the horizon. The lack of leadership at this point is immeasurable to anything we have ever seen before in human history. The stock market wouldn’t be in this state if our government had recognized that the issue at hand was as serious as it is when the first case came to America on January 19th. South Korea and America got their first cases on the same day. Our infected have reached a staggering 245,175 people while South Korea is at roughly ten thousand with only 174 casualties. America is already projecting 200,000 potential deaths from this virus which is a majority of the people that are already infected here. We should have followed suit with Korea but our pride and stubbornness and capability to ignore the world outside the United States kept us from acting swiftly. I know that people think that this is going to die down soon hopefully and I hope so too, however I think this is still just the beginning.
This is a novel virus. We don’t know what it’s capable of evolving into yet. Thankfully other countries are tracking the virus and studying it albeit what they are finding is still pretty scary. Please research this stuff and protect yourselves. In one study in Iceland they found 40 versions of the coronavirus living in a single person. This virus DOES NOT discriminate on age, but certain blood types are apparently more or less susceptible. I don’t want to fear monger by writing this, but certain things are just not being said loud enough during this trying time. People in America have been used to feeling like nothing could ever go wrong here in our less-than-perfect economy but the truth is that we’re way behind the curve for this situation.
Thankfully there is medical progress taking place in some parts of the world and people are becoming more united over this common enemy. Doctors are putting themselves at risk to fight this and these are the people that we should have had more respect for when we were ignoring the first news about this virus when it started getting the limelight on social media.
My observation is that we could have seen this coming and we the people neglected to act not only in our government (who is absolutely at fault for this), but the people including myself that heard about this virus and didn’t take it seriously enough to start talking about it on social media to spread the word before the virus could blow up. Now it’s too late. The information about this virus could have spread like wildfire but people are just too busy entertaining themselves with serotonin and dopamine devices that feed their brains happy feelings. So, when this virus came, we chose to ignore it because it didn’t make us “feel good”. Bet we’re all feeling really good about that now.
In conclusions we are failing to do what is right in this situation. We have the technology and the capability to fight this. There is no reason that we should have this shortage of supplies in the era of 3D printing. I propose that the government send a printer to every hospital to print both masks and ventilators and any other type of equipment they may need. Amazon™ could send people at home test kits, with directions of how to test yourself so that quarantine can be maintained and people can get tested without having to expose themselves or their families to potentially infected people.
Sorry for this little rant, I know I’m no doctor and hold very little credibility for any of my ideas or statements that I have put here on blast. If your opinion is any different then that’s okay. Just wash your damn hands.
